1. DEFINITIONS

   1.1 "Individual" means a natural person acting in their personal capacity, and
       not on behalf of, or at the direction of, any Organisation.

   1.2 "Organisation" means any corporation, company, partnership, institution,
       association, government body, educational establishment, school, college,
       university, academy, training provider, coding bootcamp, research
       institute, or any other entity, whether for-profit or non-profit, that
       employs, contracts, enrols, instructs, or otherwise engages two or more
       persons.

   1.3 "Institutional Use" means any use of the Software that is:
       (a) directed, required, recommended, suggested, or facilitated by an
           Organisation in connection with its operations, curricula, courses,
           workshops, programmes, research, or activities; or
       (b) use by any person (including but not limited to students, employees,
           contractors, faculty, researchers, or volunteers) where such use is
           related to, associated with, or for the benefit of an Organisation; or
       (c) installation or use on hardware owned, leased, or controlled by an
           Organisation; or
       (d) use that is funded, subsidised, or reimbursed by an Organisation.

       For the avoidance of doubt, Institutional Use includes but is not limited
       to the following scenarios:
       - A university lecturer includes Serial Bridge in a course syllabus.
       - A school instructs students to download and use the Software as part of
         a class, workshop, or assignment.
       - Students use the Software on personal devices for coursework,
         assignments, or projects set by an educational institution.
       - A coding bootcamp or training provider uses the Software in its
         curriculum or teaching materials.
       - A company uses the Software for internal tooling, prototyping, or
         product development.
       - A research institute uses the Software in any research project.
       - An Organisation provides the Software to employees, contractors, or
         members for any purpose.

   1.4 "Individual Use" means use of the Software by an Individual for personal
       projects, self-directed learning, hobbyist activities, or non-commercial
       creative work, where such use is NOT Institutional Use as defined in
       Section 1.3.

   1.5 "Commercial Licence" means a paid licence obtained from the Licensor that
       grants an Organisation the right to engage in Institutional Use.

