2. GRANT OF LICENCE

   2.1 Individual Use Licence (Free)
       Subject to the terms of this Agreement, the Licensor grants You a
       non-exclusive, non-transferable, non-sublicensable, revocable, worldwide
       licence to download, install, and use the Software free of charge solely
       for Individual Use.

   2.2 Institutional Use Licence (Paid)
       Any Institutional Use requires a valid Commercial Licence. Organisations
       must contact the Licensor to obtain a Commercial Licence before any
       Institutional Use commences.

       An Organisation may NOT circumvent this requirement by:
       (a) instructing, encouraging, or permitting individuals to download the
           Software on their own personal devices or accounts;
       (b) framing Institutional Use as "optional" or "recommended" rather than
           "required";
       (c) providing indirect access to the Software through any intermediary;
       (d) claiming that because individuals downloaded the Software independently,
           no Commercial Licence is needed; or
       (e) any other means designed to avoid the Commercial Licence requirement.

   2.3 Evaluation Period
       Organisations may evaluate the Software for a period of thirty (30)
       calendar days from first installation without a Commercial Licence, solely
       for the purpose of assessing whether to purchase a Commercial Licence.
       Continued use beyond this period constitutes a breach of this Agreement.

